	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Okay... here is the fruit of a great deal of time, research, and questing for this item.  First and foremost, as it is not mentioned in any other post i saw, Red V only spawns a few times a day unless his spawn is TRIGGERED.  You may say, well I have seen him spawn 5 times in a row and I did nothing to trigger his spawn, but there is an explanation.  Once his spawn is triggered by a player EVERY TIME that player ever enters Ak Anon Red V will again be triggered.  So, here is the bullsmasher quest from the beginning:<BR>
    1. Go to the windmills in Steamfont Mts and kill rogue (not runaway) clockworks until you get two black boxes (not rusted black boxes).  Take the two black boxes to Manik, the only gnome in full plate in Gemchopper Hall, the Gnomish warriors guild.  After this Red V will spawn a LOT... I had trouble killing enough obsoletes to keep up with all the boxes I was looting from him.  <BR>
    2.  Ask Manik &quot;Who is Red 5&quot; (not who is Red V).  This may not be required to complete the quest, but it cannot hurt.<BR>
    3.  Go down to the junkyard/necro guild (funny how the two go together hehe) and start killing Obsolete Models.  If you do not know where this is, ask a guide... they are the one good thing about this strange city.  Walk around in the maze of a guildhall until you find a room with three gnomish necromancers, dressed exactly alike and buffing skeletons.  To the left (when you are facing the necros) of this room there is another room that has a lava lamp in the corner.  Red V spawns right next to that lava lamp.  Other obsolete models will occassionally spawn in his place... kill them and loot the black box fragments.  Red V varies between lvl 4 and 7.  When you kill Red V he will drop an Incomplete Black Box.  <BR>
    3.  Combine four fragments in this box to create a Rusted Black Box.  Take this box back to Manik in Gemchopper Hall and give it to him.  He will give you patchwork boots, tunics, gloves, greaves, rusty warhammers, rusty maces, Iony's Absorber (+5 sv disease, +5 sv magic), or the Bull Smasher.  It is a RARE drop so be patient.  Stats are 6 damage, 20 delay, +2 dex, +2 str, and +2 agi I believe.  I attack almost twice as often as most NPCs I fight with this weapon!!  I LOVE it!!!<BR>
    And just a bit of helpful info... do NOT kill the skeletons in the necro guild!  Saw a lvl 30 ranger get whacked by NPCs for killing just one.  It was fairly amusing, honestly!  Red V will run to the exit if he is hurt and he is KOS outside of the guild, so don't chase him... wait for him to come running back for more!  Faction means NOTHING!!  I started Threateningly and ended Warmly, having never gotten the weapon, which brings me to my final point... after nearly 200 attempts I was near giving up when I asked my wife (a lvl 6 gnomish mage) to try the quest for me.  On her second try she got the Bull Smasher!!!  Happy?  Mad?  Jealous?  Dumbfounded?  Yes, all of those!!!  Anyway, just thought I might let you know that it may just be easier to get this weapon if you are a gnome.  I know dwarves who have gotten it, but after all when you ask Manik &quot;What is a Bull Smasher?&quot;  he does say &quot;I am willing to reward young GNOME WARRIORS blah, blah, blah...&quot;  Hope this helped!!<BR>
<BR>
Herculis, Faithful servant of Brell.  May our Lord's wisdom guide your heart to kindness and his strength guide your swordarm (my Bull Smasher arm hehe) to vengeance!    <BR>
    <BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
